source.description: Financial Industry Business Ontology (FIBO) - Full production RDF from EDM Council GitHub repository

entities.name: BoardAgreement
entities.description: formal, legally binding agreement between members of the Board of Directors of the organization

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: JointStockCompany
entities.description: for-profit, unincorporated business that has some characteristics of a corporation and some features of a partnership, with ownership interests represented by shares of stock

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: PrivatelyHeldCompany
entities.description: corporation whose issued shares are all held by a family or a small group of investors and, therefore, cannot be bought by the public

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: ReligiousCorporation
entities.description: not-for-profit corporation whose objective is specific to some fundamental set of beliefs and practices generally agreed upon by a number of people, and that is incorporated under the law

entities.name: CommonInterestDevelopmentCorporation
entities.description: not-for-profit corporation set up under specific state legislation as a business entity for homeowners' associations

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: Corporation
entities.description: formal organization that is a legal entity (artificial person) distinct from its owners, created under the jurisdiction of the laws of a state or nation

entities.name: ForProfitCorporation
entities.description: corporation whose objective is to make money, i.e., to ensure realization of a financial benefit such that the amount of revenue gained from a business activity exceeds the expenses, costs and taxes needed to sustain that activity

entities.name: Division
entities.description: part of an organization, such as a line of business, that may have separate accounting and reporting requirements

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: NotForProfitOrganization
entities.description: organization that uses its surplus revenues to further achieve its purpose rather than distributing its surplus income to the organization's owners (directors, investors, and equivalents) as profit / dividends

entities.name: OrganizationCoveringAgreement
entities.description: contract between the principals in a formal organization that specifies the relationship between the principals, and between the principals and the entity

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: BusinessEntity
entities.description: entity that is formed and administered as per commercial law in order to engage in business activities

entities.name: LegallyCompetentNaturalPerson
entities.description: person who is considered competent, under the circumstances, to enter into a contract, conduct business, or participate in other activities that generally require the mental ability to understand problems and make decisions on his or her own behalf

entities.name: NotForProfitObjective
entities.description: objective that reflects the charitable, educational, religious, humanitarian, public services, or other not for profit goals of an organization

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: ProfitObjective
entities.description: objective that reflects pursuit of a financial benefit that may be realized when the amount of revenue gained from a business activity exceeds the expenses, costs and taxes needed to sustain that activity

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: ReligiousObjective
entities.description: not-for-profit objective that reflects the religious goals of an organization

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

description._: legal entity whose shareholders are entitled to a percentage of a named company's profits via a private contract

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: Goal
entities.description: desired result that a party envisions, plans, and to which it commits, in order to achieve a desired state

entities.name: InvestmentObjective
entities.description: financial objective used by an investor to determine whether or not a given potential investment is appropriate for themselves or on behalf of another party

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: Objective
entities.description: short-term, quantitative, measurable result that a party seeks to attain in order to achieve its long-term goals

entities.name: SalesStrategy
entities.description: strategy for selling something, including allocating resources to the sales process, reducing costs, and optimizing revenues

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: FunctionalBusinessEntity
entities.description: functional entity defined in terms of the nature of the commercial activity it conducts

description._: role of an individual or organization that is a member of an alliance set up to pool resources and share risk with respect to a large transaction

entities.name: GovernmentBody
entities.description: formal organization that is an agency, instrumentality, or other body of a supranational, national, federal, state, or local government, including certain multijurisdictional agencies and departments that carry out the business of government

entities.name: TribalEntity
entities.description: legal entity that represents fundamental unit of sovereign tribal (indigenous) government

entities.name: ArticlesOfIncorporation
entities.description: contract that establishes a new corporation or, when amended, adjusts the legal basis for the corporation, and outlines basic information about the corporation, including the type of business, and a description of the business' operational characteristics

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: BoardMembership
entities.description: situation relating an individual member of the board of directors to the organization

entities.name: Bylaws
entities.description: written rules for conduct of a corporation, association, partnership or any organization

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: ChiefExecutiveOfficer
entities.description: top corporate officer responsible for an organization's overall operations and performance

entities.name: ChiefFinancialOfficer
entities.description: senior-most corporate officer responsible for financial control and planning for an organization or project

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: NonExecutiveBoardMember
entities.description: member of the board of directors of an organization that has no executive responsibilities towards the running of that organization

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: PrincipalParty
entities.description: controlling party that is responsible for the management of daily business operations of an organization

entities.name: Signatory
entities.description: responsible party authorized to sign agreements on behalf of themselves, another person, or an organization

entities.name: LegallyCapableAdult
entities.description: person who has attained the age of majority as defined in some jurisdiction and who is allowed to conduct a business or any other occupation on his or her own behalf or for their own account

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

description._: classifier for an event (milestone), or set of events related to the status or level of completion of a designated activity, task, or segment of work required for contract fulfillment

entities.name: MilestoneEvent
entities.description: event related to the status or level of completion of a designated activity, task, or segment of work required for contract fulfillment

entities.name: TermSheet
entities.description: nonbinding agreement setting forth the basic terms and conditions under which a proposed business deal may be made

entities.name: UseOfProceedsProvision
entities.description: contract provision specifying how funds obtained through financing, such as through a credit agreement, offering, warrant, or other instrument are intended to be used

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: AccountingFramework
entities.description: framework, including policies, methods, rules, and processes, used to measure, recognize, present, and disclose the information appearing in an entity's financial statements, and, from a legal ownership perspective, that is applied for accounting consolidation determination

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: ContractuallyCapableEntity
entities.description: a unique entity that is legally or financially responsible for the performance of financial transactions, or has the legal right in its jurisdiction to enter independently into legal contracts, regardless of whether it is incorporated or constituted in some other way (e.g. trust, partnership, contractual). This excludes natural persons, but includes governmental organizations and supranationals.

entities.name: Policy
entities.description: system of principles, rules and guidelines, adopted by an organization to guide decision making with respect to particular situations and implemented via procedures or protocols to achieve stated goals

entities.name: SignatoryCapacity
entities.description: the capacity of some natural person to sign agreements on the part of some organization or legal person

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: MajorityControllingParty
entities.description: controlling party that possesses, either directly or indirectly, the power to direct or cause the direction of the management and policies of a legal person, whether through the ownership of a majority of voting securities, by contract, or otherwise

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: EntityOwner
entities.description: owner (person, group of people, or other business entity) that owns, or holds an ownership interest in, a formal business organization

entities.name: EntityOwnership
entities.description: ownership by some party of an interest in some non-governmental formal organization

entities.name: ForeignBranchOwnership
entities.description: ownership by some party of some formal organization or organizational sub-unit that is a foreign affiliate and legally part of the owning entity

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: InvestmentEquity
entities.description: equity that represents an ownership interest in some entity, but may or may not take the form of shareholders's equity

entities.name: InvestorContract
entities.description: Contract setting out the terms under which some investor invests in the entity and setting out the rights which are conferred on that investor.

entities.name: UltimateConsolidation
entities.description: highest-level (top, end) ancestral ownership, evidenced by accounting consolidation, by some party of some other legal entity

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: Employee
entities.description: person in the service of another under any contract of hire, express or implied, oral or written, where the employer has the right to control and direct that person in the material details of how the work is to be performed

entities.name: GeneralPartner
entities.description: partner and part-owner that is responsible for managing the day to day operations of the partnership and that may be jointly and severally liable for the obligations of the partnership

relationships.name: hasDealtCurrency
relationships.description: specifies a unit of currency representing the exchanged (target) currency in an exchange rate; R units of this currency represent one unit of the base currency

relationships.name: hasGoal
relationships.description: relates something to a long-term, desired outcome

relationships.name: hasObjective
relationships.description: relates something to a specific objective (result) that it aims to achieve within a time frame and with available resources

relationships.name: causes
relationships.description: relationship between an event or set of events or factors (the cause) and a second event, phenomenon, situation, or result (the effect), where the second event or outcome is understood as a consequence of the first

relationships.name: controls
relationships.description: exercises authority or influence over

relationships.name: holds
relationships.description: is the relationship between a party and something it possesses, or over which it exercises some ownership or control or has at its discretion the ability to dispose of it as it sees fit

relationships.name: isCausedBy
relationships.description: is the relationship between an event (the effect) and a second event (the cause), where the first event is understood as a consequence of the second; also, the relationship between a set of factors (causes) and a phenomenon (the effect)

relationships.name: isProducedBy
relationships.description: identifies the producer that fabricates, manufactures or otherwise creates something through some production process

relationships.name: manages
relationships.description: manages relationship

relationships.name: produces
relationships.description: creates through a fabrication, manufacturing or production process

relationships.name: hasFullSovereigntyOver
relationships.description: relates a polity to a geopolitical entity where the polity has absolute, supreme and ultimate dominion and authority of a political state subject to no higher power, expressed within its territory in full self-government and in complete freedom from any outside influence

relationships.name: authorizes
relationships.description: endorses, enables, empowers, or gives permission to

relationships.name: authorizesThrough
relationships.description: indicates the situation that facilitates designation of an authorized party by the authorizing party for some purpose

relationships.name: hasAuthorizingParty
relationships.description: indicates the party that endorses, enables, empowers, or gives permission in the situation

relationships.name: hasStreetAddress
relationships.description: indicates a fully-specified address component that consists of a primary address number, predirectional, street name, suffix, postdirectional, and an optional secondary unit

relationships.name: hasLegalAddress
relationships.description: indicates the legal address for the entity, in the jurisdiction in which the entity is established, used for registration purposes with respect to obtaining an LEI

relationships.name: isDirectlyConsolidatedBy
relationships.description: indicates that the entity considered the 'end node' or consolidating entity (parent) fully consolidates the accounting of the 'start node' (child) per the accounting rules specified, and is the closest consolidating entity to that child in any applicable ownership hierarchy

relationships.name: isInternationalBranchOf
relationships.description: indicates that the entity considered the 'start node' or consolidated entity (child) is an international subsidiary of the 'end node' (parent) in the jurisdiction of the child

relationships.name: isUltimatelyConsolidatedBy
relationships.description: indicates that the entity considered the 'end node' or consolidating entity (parent) fully consolidates the accounting of the 'start node' (child) per the accounting rules specified, and is the most distant consolidating entity to that child in any applicable ownership hierarchy

relationships.name: implements
relationships.description: carries out or puts into effect, fulfills

relationships.name: licenses
relationships.description: issues a license required in order to perform some task, provide some service, exercise some privilege, or pursue some line of business or occupation to some party

relationships.name: hasMajorityControllingParty
relationships.description: indicates a party that owns a controlling stake (over 50 percent) in the entity

relationships.name: hasInvestmentEntity
relationships.description: relates a legal person to a directly owned formal organization or subsidiary, depending on the percent ownership interest

relationships.name: hasInvestmentOwnership
relationships.description: relates a legal person to the context in which it owns a formal organization

relationships.name: hasOwningEntity
relationships.description: indicates a party that owns a formal organization

relationships.name: hasAffiliate
relationships.description: has a party which directly, or indirectly through one or more intermediaries, controls, or is controlled by, or is under common control with the company

relationships.name: hasSubsidiary
relationships.description: relates a legal entity to another organization that it owns at least 50 percent of

relationships.name: isAffiliateOf
relationships.description: relates a party which directly, or indirectly through one or more intermediaries, controls, or is controlled by, or is under common control by another party to that party

relationships.name: isControllingAffiliateOf
relationships.description: controls directly, or indirectly through one or more intermediaries

relationships.name: isParentCompanyOf
relationships.description: indicates a controlled affiliate that it owns at least 50 percent of

relationships.name: isOwnedBy
relationships.description: indicates something that someone owns

relationships.name: owns
relationships.description: indicates something that a party holds title to and may possess

relationships.name: ownsAsset
relationships.description: identifies an asset that an owner owns

relationships.name: isGeneralPartnerOf
relationships.description: indicates the organization that the general partner manages

relationships.name: isOwnedAndControlledBy
relationships.description: relates something to the party that owns, influences, manages and directs it

relationships.name: ownsAndControls
relationships.description: directs and exercises authoritative or dominating influence over some thing that is also owned

relationships.name: hasPrincipalExecutiveOfficeAddress
relationships.description: relates an organization, specifically the issuer of a financial instrument, to its principal executive address, as required for issuance of that instrument

description._: indicates the nature of the pricing quotations to be requested from banks and/or dealers when determining the market value of the reference obligation for purposes of cash settlement
specifies the initial date in a range of dates by which the underlying asset (or some portion thereof) must be delivered in order for the terms of the contract to be fulfilled

relationships.name: operatesInCountry
relationships.description: indicates the ISO 3166-1 country in which an exchange, data reporting services provider, or crypto asset services provider operates

relationships.name: operatesInMunicipality
relationships.description: indicates the municipality or business center in which in which an exchange, data reporting services provider, or crypto asset services provider operates

relationships.name: facilitates
relationships.description: acts as an enabler in a situation in which an event, a task, a conversation or something else occurs

relationships.name: buys
relationships.description: links a party in the role of purchaser to something that they have purchased or plan to purchase

relationships.name: buysFrom
relationships.description: links a party in the role of purchaser to a party from which they have made or are planning to make a purchase

relationships.name: sells
relationships.description: links a party in the role of broker, dealer, vendor, or merchandiser to something that they make available for sale

relationships.name: sellsTo
relationships.description: links a party in the role of broker, dealer, vendor, or merchandiser to a purchaser or potential purchasing party

relationships.name: regulatesSupplyOf
relationships.description: relates a regulatory agency to something it controls or supervises the availability of in some market by means of rules and regulations

relationships.name: hasAppraiser
relationships.description: relates an assessment or report to an agent that conducts the assessment

relationships.name: hasFirstTradeSettlementDate
relationships.description: indicates the date on which the first trade of a newly issued security is settled

relationships.name: hasOrganizationMember
relationships.description: hasOrganizationMember relationship
